  "body": "**What happened**:\r\n\r\nIf  `debug` is added to a server configuration but not the last one in the Corefile, debug statements won't be printed.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nI'd expect the debug mode to be enabled if `debug` plugin is used in any server configuration.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nUse the following Corefile:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexample.net {\r\n    hosts\r\n    debug\r\n}\r\n\r\n. {\r\n    whoami\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOutput is:\r\n\r\n```\r\n.:1053\r\nexample.net.:1053\r\nCoreDNS-1.7.0\r\nlinux/amd64, go1.14.3, 2d5f12d4\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith this Corefile (where `debug` is used in the last server config):\r\n\r\n```\r\nexample.net {\r\n    hosts\r\n}\r\n\r\n. {\r\n    whoami\r\n    debug\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nit will print debug statements for the `hosts` plugin.\r\n\r\n```\r\n[DEBUG] plugin/hosts: Parsed hosts file into 0 entries\r\n.:1053\r\nexample.net.:1053\r\nCoreDNS-1.7.0\r\nlinux/amd64, go1.14.3, 2d5f12d4\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n\r\n- the version of CoreDNS: 1.7.0\r\n- Corefile: see above\r\n- logs, if applicable: see above\r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`): Fedora 32\r\n- Others:\r\n",
